Date: Mon, 8 Jun 2026 11:11:12 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 01/14] sourcing_reference: collapse Sourcing into Quotation
 pipeline stage (19.0.1.1.0)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The pipeline is simplified from 9 stages to 8 — the standalone Sourcing
stage has been removed, and Quotation now covers both the merchandiser's
internal RFQ work and outbound client quoting. Reference-ID generation
moves from Incoming-Inquiry-exit to Quotation-entry to match.

  * data/crm_stage_data.xml — remove crm_stage_sourcing, renumber rest
  * hooks.py — drop sourcing entry from stage adoption + cleanup maps
  * models/crm_lead.py — rename _is_sourcing_stage to _is_quotation_stage,
    reroute the ID generator trigger
  * models/project_project.py — fix fallback SO lookup to use
    order_line.project_id and gate behind 'sale_order_id' in vals
  * migrations/19.0.1.1.0/ — schema/data migration to drop Sourcing stage
